					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Sometimes you can come up with interesting tricks and approximations, too. Depends on the number.
<br />
<br />(N / 7) - (N &gt;&gt; 3) ~= N / 56. As for dividing by 7, one could make a lookup table like: 7^1, 7^2, 7^3, etc and loop subtraction.
<br />
<br />There are also approximation algorithms that have rounding errors of +/- 1, like multiplying and then shifting the result right.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

