					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">h^2 = b^2 + c^2
<br />tan a = b/c
<br />
<br />There is no other way to do it (without inacurate aproximations), else mathematicians would have found it out for ages. In fact I have a routine in my game where I calculate something complicated involving square and roots (for enemies shooting homing projectiles at constant speed), I've used an algorithm I found on 6502.org to compute the root and it works well, better than any lockup table.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Life is complex: it has both real and imaginary components.</div>
